General.Name: Kopy Goldfields publ AB
General.Description: Kopy Goldfields AB (publ) operates as a gold exploration and production company in Sweden. The company focuses on the exploration, evaluation, and production of gold and silver deposits in the Khabarovsk region, the Bodaibo district of the Irkutsk region of Russia, and the Khakassia of the Russian Federation. It holds interests in the Krasny gold project comprising three bedrock licenses and one alluvial gold license located in the Irkutsk region of Russia. The company operated two bedrock mines, such as the Yubileyniy and Perevalnoe; and placer the Buor-Sala and Khayarylakh placer located in the Khabarovsk region of Russia. The company is headquartered in Stockholm, Sweden.
